Optional: Preheat oven to 200 degrees for warming pancakes later on. Wash and dry all produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Zest 1 @Sunkist® Blood Orange{1} until you have 2 tsp; peel @Sunkist® Blood Orange{2}(peeled), removing as much white pith as possible. Thinly slice peeled oranges crosswise into rounds.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Set aside for pancake batter in step 5.

Set aside 1 packet crème fraîche for pancake batter.

== Lemon Crème Fraîche ==

In a second small #bowl{}, combine @crème fraîche{7%tbsp}, ¼ tsp lemon zest, ½ tsp sugar, a squeeze of lemon juice, and pinch of salt to taste.

== Toasted Almonds ==

Heat a medium, dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @almonds{1%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly toasted, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer almonds to a #plate{} to cool. Wipe out pan.

== Syrup ==

Heat pan used for almonds over medium-high heat. Add @cherry jam{8%tbsp} and @maple syrup{8%tbsp}. Cook until bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{3%tbsp}(solid) until melted. Add a couple squeezes of lemon juice (save at least 1 wedge for pancake batter) and a big pinch of salt. Set aside.

== Spinach-Orange Salad ==

In a large bowl, combine @Honey Dijon Dressing{3%ounce} with orange zest to taste. Add @spinach{5%ounce}, half the sliced oranges, half the @feta cheese{1%cup}, and half the almonds. Toss until well combined; season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Transfer salad to a #serving platter{}. Sprinkle with remaining sliced oranges, feta, and almonds.

== Pancakes ==

In a medium bowl, whisk together @milk{6.75%ounce}, @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, @eggs{2}, melted @butter{2%tbsp}, 1 tsp lemon zest, juice from 1 lemon wedge, and reserved @crème fraîche{1%tbsp}.

In a second large bowl, combine @tempura mix{246%g}, @sugar{1/4%cup}, and ½ tsp salt. Whisk in milk mixture until just combined.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium heat.

Add a few ¼-cup scoops of batter to pan. Once bubbles form on tops of pancakes (about ~{1-2%minutes}), flip and cook until golden, ~{30-60%seconds} more.

Transfer to a plate. If you want to keep your pancakes nice and warm, transfer to a #baking sheet{} as you make them; place in preheated oven until ready to serve.

Repeat process with remaining batter, adding more oil between batches if necessary.

> TIP: For quicker cooking, use 2 nonstick pans, or a griddle if you have one.

== Assembly ==

Warm syrup over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide pancakes between plates; top with syrup, @walnuts{1.5%ounce}, and a dollop of lemony crème fraîche. Serve spinach salad on the side.

> Alternatively, set up a toppings bar: Serve the syrup, walnuts, and crème fraîche in individual bowls and let everyone assemble as they please. For pickier eaters, serve pancakes with butter or simply sprinkle with powdered sugar.